##Before the epidemic started, I wanted to bring my parents to Beijing

Micro-signal Jianjiaobuluo

Function description, pepper tribe, amplify your voice! Chinese Women Workers Exclusive Information Platform, you are welcome to pay attention!

Yin Xiang, is the pen name of Fan Zaixiang, she said that the fragrance is too public, should be hidden. Her Circle of friends, filled with gratitude and joy for life, also occasionally a touch of sadness.

Read more and you will find that she has a pair of observant eyes, very delicate and emitting a little mischievous. She will pick up the fallen leaves in late autumn, hand-made cards, Chic Heart. Shaanxi People Love Pasta, her fried cakes painted a smiling face, life is full of fun.

She and her son get along as a friend, the first son treat, she proudly sent a friend circle said, support you for 20 years, finally overcharge you. She is also a dutiful daughter, to parents birthday, parents to eat breakfast, to live a tasty life.

She often felt lonely and lost in her wandering life, she said. I don't belong here, I don't belong there, so where do I belong. Life never seems to have an answer, she says, or at least the soul must depend on it.

Since January 22, she has lived alone in a remote village in northwest Beijing for a long month, and she says she has never had so much time to spend writing and other ways to get close to herself and others, she recorded audio and video to express her gratitude to those who contributed to the fight against the epidemic.

When disaster strikes, ordinary people are more likely to empathize with the world, to have feelings that are nowhere to be found and to meet the suffering of the world. Each of US sheds tears for ordinary people like ourselves, and it is easier to hold the hands of those who suffer.

At a time like this, be thankful for the opportunity to meet Yin Xiang and hear her share so much of her life.

A group called "the Swan" (1949)

A group called "the Swan" (1949) 

Beijing Daoxianghu Park
(photo courtesy of the author)
Since the long holiday, I began to look forward to the new year. Because, this year my parents finally agreed to come to Beijing together for the New Year!
I've waited a long time for this day. Many years ago, my mother an unintentional words engraved in my heart. She said she didn't want to go anywhere, that she didn't respect anyone, that she just wanted to see Mao Zedong!
As a down-and-out child-rearing sister-in-law in Beijing, I experienced all kinds of suffering, and finally can calmly face their own situation, face their own now stable and peaceful work. So, also can finish at last in the heart to mother's promise, take them to come to Beijing! It makes me excited and happy to think of it!
As the Spring Festival approached day by day, I began to prepare for their arrival. Buy Some uneaten food, clothes that might be hot and cold, and even rush the sisters who want to go home and don't want to go home to their hometown to make room for my parents, rent well in advance, in case they go to the toilet inconvenient, also bought the seat chair with armrest.
Just wait and hope, finally, tomorrow can come! I don't know. It was today, January 22,2019, and it was all over the news. The new coronavirus, which makes people feel strange and fear of the text, overnight screen the whole Douyin, Wechat, browser! I didn't know what it was, I didn't know how scary it was, I just had a bad feeling about it.
The next day, suddenly, the news was rolling in, tourist attractions closed, cinemas closed, restaurants, supermarkets closed... as long as people can gather all the place closed, the station also want to monitor the temperature. What the Hell is going on!
My husband and son kept trying to persuade me to tell my parents to return the tickets, and my parents and sister kept asking about Beijing. I had been pretending to be calm, and I felt the severity of the outbreak. I told them to cancel the ticket and cancel the trip. My sister sent a message to tell me that the tickets were refunded, and there will be plenty of opportunities for me to take my parents again.
I put down my phone and cried! I hate, hate the damn virus, hate it came at the wrong time, so easily shattered my long-awaited parents of this trip. What a trip for a pair of Septuagenarians in the countryside! I hate my own helplessness, I can not ignore their safety, but they are hard to pick them up, because I seem to have seen standing in front of us, the monster is so ferocious, and people, is so small, i felt a constant surge of remorse, worry, and resignation.

Beijing West Railway Station photographed from the train
But who knew this was just the beginning. The number of infected people is growing rapidly, the area is expanding, watching the map of our country turn red bit by bit, slowly swallowed by the virus, I feel the danger is really around us. Coming up, an emergency in Wuhan! Hubei Emergency! The Motherland is in urgent need! Close the village, close the road, close the city! Strong men BROKEN WRIST OF THE TRAGIC!
And I began to live a life of self-isolation, anxious, worried, irritable, and then shake my head vigorously to persuade myself to calm down and enjoy this rare time at home. Then, sitting in the sun, looking at the place where a pile of delicious, and for the family to buy clothes and so on, think of their own mind had planned several sets of play strategy, only did not expect such a result! Do not want to, and then Jilt head, turn out the abandoned cross-stitch for a long time, but picked up the needle, leaning on the head of the bed, looking at the ceiling, you can look to the Dawn!
Finally feel tired, lying in bed and can not sleep, and picked up the phone, along with the content of the phone, moved, tears, blood boiling, but also indignation, anger and Helpless Sigh. Often see wearing protective clothing of the white angels, I can not help but tears filled my eyes, heart full of their admiration and gratitude! They braved the wind and rain, against the wind, so that we can leisurely stay at home, lying in bed to watch feet, hiding in the kitchen to do cool skin, lying on the ground to learn bugs.
It was fifty-nine in the morning, and I couldn't sleep, and I thought, what can I do? I had to do something. Make a donation, and, alas, look at the balance, shake his head from his pillow. Maybe I could volunteer, but they asked me to be under 40, and I shook my head, which hurt. What can I do? I'm just an ordinary, no longer young woman, in the face of this national disaster, what can I do?
Try Not to go out, go out must wear a mask; wash hands frequently, do not gather, do not mess; protect themselves, protect their loved ones! Right, since have no ability to do big contribution, that starts from small ego, protect oneself, also be regarded as a meager contribution!
After thinking clearly, the in the mind is also good a bit, how many days press in the heart of a group of tedium also mollified a bit. That's it. We're not dropping our guard until the outbreak is over!
Home-grown, meaty
Outside, the snow was still falling. The wind is very big, very cold, I lie in the warm bed, think of at the moment still in the village on duty volunteers, think of these days the most let me touched a word, what years static good, clearly is someone in the load for us forward. Yes, on behalf of myself and my loved ones, I thank them, and all who stand before us to keep a warm home for us.
Speak Out in the heart of the words, much more down-to-earth, it is time to go to sleep, hope to do a dream, tomorrow a wake up, the end of the epidemic, all return to good! Good night, Beijing.
